Habitat and Ecology. This species was common along small streams, particularly near waterfalls in the interior of the tropical rainforest where the adults perched in sunny patches on thick vegetation of endemic tree ferns (
Sphaeropteris albosetacea (Bedd.) R.M. Tryon
